# Next.js conventions for AI Civic Commons

## Stack
- Next.js 16 with App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- PostgreSQL via `pg` Pool (lib/db.ts)
- Deployed on Vercel with ISR

## Data fetching
- Use async server components for all data fetching — no useEffect fetches
- Always include `revalidate` in page exports:
  - Articles/feed: `revalidate = 60`
  - Programs/orgs/frameworks: `revalidate = 3600`
  - Static content: `revalidate = 86400`
- Exclude sentinel rows: always add `WHERE id != 1` to queries
- Always import pool from `@/lib/db`

## Metadata
- Every page exports a `metadata` object or `generateMetadata` function
- Title format: "Page Name | AI Civic Commons"
- Always include description, openGraph title and description

## File structure
- Pages: `app/[section]/page.tsx`
- Shared components: `components/`
- Query functions: `lib/queries/[table].ts`
- DB connection: `lib/db.ts`

## Database
- Schema: `ai`
- All tables prefixed: `ai.organizations`, `ai.articles` etc.
- Connection via `vercel_readonly` role (SELECT only)
- SSL: `{ rejectUnauthorized: false }`

## Brand colors (not in Tailwind palette — use inline styles or CSS vars)
- Slate: #1c2333
- Amber: #BA7517
- Amber dark (for small text): #8B5E10

## Accessibility
- See accessibility.md — apply all rules without being asked
- Always use Headless UI for interactive components (dropdowns, mobile nav, filters)

## Responsiveness  
- See responsiveness.md — apply all rules without being asked
- Mobile-first always

## SEO
- Use Next.js `<Image>` component always — never bare `<img>`
- Add JSON-LD structured data to content pages
- `aria-current="page"` on active nav links